===Etymology===
Possibly from {{Sp.}} [[Komantcia]], a corruption of Ute[[Kohmaht]] "enemy" or "strangers". Alternatively from the Spanish [[camino ancho]] "wide trail". The Comanches' own preferred name is Numunuu, meaning "the People".

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# An [[amerind]] [[ethnic group]] of [[North America]], especially of [[Texas]] and [[Oklahoma]].
# The [[nation]] of the Comanche people.
# The [[Uto-Aztecan]] [[language]] spoken by these people, sometimes classified as a [[Shoshone]] dialect.
# A light [[single]]-[[engine]] [[aircraft]], the [[w:Piper PA-24 Comanche|Piper PA-24 Comanche]].
# A [[military]] [[helicopter]], the [[w:RAH-66 Comanche|RAH-66 Comanche]].

